WEBVTT

00:17.977 --> 00:20.312
MARY: Come on, let's say
good night to your brother.

00:25.109 --> 00:26.235
DEAN: Night, Sam.

00:27.111 --> 00:28.320
MARY: Good night, love.

00:30.740 --> 00:31.782
Hey, Dean.

00:32.199 --> 00:34.410
-Daddy!
-Hey, buddy. Woah.

00:34.618 --> 00:37.037
So what do you think? You think
Sammy's ready to toss around a football?

00:37.121 --> 00:38.748
-No, Daddy.
-No.

00:39.290 --> 00:40.499
-You got him?
-I got him.

00:43.461 --> 00:44.545
Sweet dreams, Sam.

00:44.628 --> 00:45.629
(BABY COOING)

01:09.945 --> 01:11.864
(BABY FUSSING OVER MONITOR)

01:16.118 --> 01:17.161
John.

01:17.536 --> 01:18.579
(SIGHING)

01:37.973 --> 01:39.058
John?

01:39.183 --> 01:42.561
-Is he hungry?
-Shh.

01:42.812 --> 01:43.979
MARY: Okay.

01:45.356 --> 01:46.440
(SIGHING)

01:59.328 --> 02:00.412
Hmm.

02:05.000 --> 02:06.335
(MEN SHOUTING ON TV)

02:16.470 --> 02:17.721
(JOHN SNORING)

02:21.016 --> 02:22.893
Sammy! Sammy!

02:26.397 --> 02:27.439
(GASPING)

02:28.482 --> 02:30.526
(MARY SCREAMING)

02:30.609 --> 02:31.652
Mary?

02:32.444 --> 02:33.529
Mary!

02:36.115 --> 02:37.157
Mary!

02:38.075 --> 02:39.118
Mary!

02:46.584 --> 02:47.626
Hey, Sammy.

02:49.295 --> 02:50.379
You okay?

03:07.146 --> 03:08.898
No! Mary!

03:10.107 --> 03:11.317
(EXCLAIMING)

03:17.072 --> 03:18.115
(CRYING)

03:22.494 --> 03:23.579
DEAN: Daddy!

03:23.913 --> 03:26.749
Take your brother outside as fast
as you can. Don't look back.

03:26.832 --> 03:28.000
Now, Dean. Go!

03:31.837 --> 03:32.922
Mary!

03:34.256 --> 03:35.299
No!

03:44.058 --> 03:45.142
It's okay, Sammy.

03:48.020 --> 03:49.063
I got you.

03:57.529 --> 04:00.282
FIREFIGHTER 1: It's all right.
I got it. Move the line up.

04:02.409 --> 04:03.494
FIREFIGHTER 2: Here.

04:15.130 --> 04:17.591
FIREFIGHTER 3: Let's get a stream
on the right side.

04:17.675 --> 04:18.676
OFFICER: I got it.

04:18.759 --> 04:23.097
Hey, stay back. You have to stay back.
Come on. You have to stay on the curb.

04:36.485 --> 04:38.153
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)

04:40.280 --> 04:42.866
JESSICA: Sam. Get a move on, would you?

04:42.950 --> 04:44.994
Supposed to be there,
like, 15 minutes ago.

04:46.078 --> 04:47.871
Sam. You're coming or what?

04:48.497 --> 04:50.374
-Do I have to?
-Yes.

04:50.958 --> 04:52.001
It'll be fun.

04:53.293 --> 04:54.628
And where is your costume?

04:55.462 --> 04:56.463
(LAUGHING)

04:57.673 --> 04:59.425
You know how I feel about Halloween.

04:59.967 --> 05:01.301
(HIP HOP MUSIC PLAYING)

05:03.595 --> 05:04.763
So here's to Sam

05:04.847 --> 05:07.349
-and his awesome LSAT victory.
-All right. All right.

05:07.433 --> 05:10.602
-It's not that big a deal.
-He acts all humble, but he scored a 174.

05:10.686 --> 05:11.812
Mmm.

05:11.895 --> 05:13.480
-He's that good?
-Scary good.

05:14.148 --> 05:16.567
So, there you go.
You are a first-round draft pick.

05:17.067 --> 05:18.902
You can go to any law school you want.

05:18.986 --> 05:20.988
Actually, I got an interview here, Monday.

05:21.739 --> 05:24.700
If it goes okay, I think
I got a shot at a full ride next year.

05:24.783 --> 05:26.493
Hey. It's gonna go great.

05:27.786 --> 05:28.829
It better.

05:28.912 --> 05:31.248
How's it feel to be
the golden boy of your family?

05:31.373 --> 05:32.416
Uh, they don't know.

05:32.666 --> 05:35.002
No, I would be gloating. Why not?

05:35.377 --> 05:37.171
Because we're not exactly the Bradys.

05:37.254 --> 05:39.673
And I'm not exactly the Huxtables.
More shots?

05:39.757 --> 05:41.467
-No.
-No. No. No.

05:41.675 --> 05:44.011
Seriously, I'm proud of you.

05:44.219 --> 05:47.347
And you're gonna knock them dead
on Monday and get that full ride.

05:47.431 --> 05:48.432
I know it.

05:49.183 --> 05:50.851
What would I do without you?

05:50.934 --> 05:52.186
Crash and burn.

06:11.288 --> 06:12.331
(THUDDING)

06:41.568 --> 06:42.569
(SAM GRUNTING)

06:43.362 --> 06:44.488
(GRUNTING)

06:52.162 --> 06:53.580
Whoa, easy, tiger.

06:54.456 --> 06:55.499
Dean?

06:55.582 --> 06:56.750
(LAUGHING)

06:57.000 --> 06:58.627
You scared the crap out of me.

06:58.710 --> 07:00.462
That's cause you're out of practice.

07:00.546 --> 07:02.172
(GRUNTING)

07:02.256 --> 07:03.841
Or not.

07:03.924 --> 07:05.342
Get off me.

07:05.425 --> 07:07.344
Dean, what the hell are you doing here?

07:07.427 --> 07:09.138
Well, I was looking for a beer.

07:09.555 --> 07:10.556
Sam?

07:12.099 --> 07:13.600
Jess, hey.

07:15.435 --> 07:17.437
Dean, this is my girlfriend, Jessica.

07:18.105 --> 07:19.439
Wait. Your brother, Dean?

07:20.065 --> 07:21.150
I love the Smurfs.

07:21.775 --> 07:25.612
You know, I gotta tell you, you are
completely out of my brother's league.

07:25.696 --> 07:29.283
-Just let me put something on.
-No, no. No, I wouldn't dream of it.

07:29.366 --> 07:30.492
Seriously.

07:31.869 --> 07:33.495
Anyway, I gotta
borrow your boyfriend here,

07:33.579 --> 07:34.955
talk about some private family business.

07:35.038 --> 07:36.039
But nice meeting you.

07:38.542 --> 07:39.543
No.

07:40.043 --> 07:42.921
No. Whatever you want to say,
you can say it in front of her.

07:43.005 --> 07:44.506
Okay.

07:44.590 --> 07:47.176
Um, Dad hasn't been home in a few days.

07:48.385 --> 07:50.637
So he's working overtime
on a Miller-Time shift.

07:50.721 --> 07:52.556
He'll stumble back in sooner or later.

07:54.558 --> 07:56.018
Dad's on a hunting trip

07:56.977 --> 07:58.812
and he hasn't been home in a few days.

08:03.567 --> 08:04.860
Jess, excuse us.

08:05.527 --> 08:07.738
I mean, come on,
you can't just break in,

08:07.821 --> 08:10.240
middle of the night,
and expect me to hit the road with you.

08:10.324 --> 08:11.742
You're not hearing me, Sammy.

08:11.825 --> 08:13.994
Dad's missing.
I need you to help me find him.

08:14.077 --> 08:16.205
SAM: You remember
the poltergeist in Amherst?

08:16.288 --> 08:17.831
Or the Devil's Gates in Clifton?

08:17.915 --> 08:20.500
He was missing then too.
He's always missing and he's always fine.

08:20.584 --> 08:21.585
Not for this long.

08:21.668 --> 08:23.128
Now, you gonna come with me or not?

08:23.212 --> 08:25.339
-I'm not.
-Why not?

08:25.422 --> 08:27.633
I swore I was done hunting. For good.

08:28.091 --> 08:29.927
Come on, it wasn't easy,
but it wasn't that bad.

08:30.010 --> 08:31.011
Yeah?

08:31.094 --> 08:34.514
When I told Dad I was scared of the thing
in my closet he gave me a .45.

08:34.598 --> 08:35.891
What was he supposed to do?

08:35.974 --> 08:37.517
I was nine years old.

08:38.101 --> 08:40.646
He was supposed to say,
"Don't be afraid of the dark."

08:40.729 --> 08:42.397
"Don't be afraid of the dark"?
What you kidding me?

08:42.481 --> 08:45.234
Of course you should be afraid
of the dark. You know what's out there.

08:45.317 --> 08:47.444
Yeah, I know. But still, the way we
grew up, after Mom was killed,

08:47.527 --> 08:49.863
and Dad's obsession
to find the thing that killed her.

08:49.947 --> 08:51.949
But we still haven't found the damn thing.

08:52.032 --> 08:53.867
So we kill everything we can find.

08:54.117 --> 08:55.744
Save a lot of people doing it too.

08:58.413 --> 09:00.540
You think Mom would have
wanted this for us?

09:02.793 --> 09:03.877
The weapon training?

09:04.378 --> 09:06.463
And melting the silver into bullets?

09:06.713 --> 09:09.091
Man, Dean, we were raised like warriors.

09:09.174 --> 09:12.970
So what are you gonna do? You're just
gonna live some normal, apple-pie life?

09:13.053 --> 09:15.722
-Is that it?
-No. Not normal. Safe.

09:16.348 --> 09:18.892
And that's why you ran away. I see.

09:18.976 --> 09:20.435
I was just going to college.

09:20.519 --> 09:23.313
It was Dad who said if I was
gonna go, I should stay gone.

09:23.939 --> 09:25.232
And that's what I'm doing.

09:25.315 --> 09:27.150
Well, Dad's in real trouble right now.

09:27.234 --> 09:29.152
If he's not dead already. I can feel it.

09:31.863 --> 09:33.156
I can't do this alone.

09:33.282 --> 09:34.616
Yes, you can.

09:34.700 --> 09:37.119
Yeah. Well, I don't want to.

09:41.081 --> 09:42.207
(SIGHING)

09:46.003 --> 09:47.045
What was he hunting?

09:53.010 --> 09:54.177
DEAN: All right.

09:54.261 --> 09:56.513
Let's see.
Where the hell did I put that thing?

09:56.596 --> 09:58.890
So when Dad left,
why didn't you go with him?

09:58.974 --> 10:02.102
I was working my own gig.
This voodoo thing down in New Orleans.

10:02.686 --> 10:04.855
Dad let you go on
a hunting trip by yourself?

10:05.856 --> 10:07.024
I'm 26, dude.

10:08.400 --> 10:09.484
All right. Here we go.

10:10.277 --> 10:12.696
So Dad was checking out
this two-lane blacktop

10:12.779 --> 10:14.656
just outside of Jericho, California.

10:14.740 --> 10:16.241
About a month ago, this guy...

10:16.325 --> 10:19.328
They found his car,
but he'd vanished, completely MIA.

10:20.579 --> 10:21.830
So maybe he was kidnapped.

10:21.997 --> 10:24.082
Yeah, well. Here's another one in April.

10:24.166 --> 10:27.919
Another in December '04, '03, '98, '92.

10:28.003 --> 10:29.755
Ten of them over the past 20 years.

10:30.464 --> 10:32.924
All men, all same
five-mile stretch of road.

10:34.843 --> 10:38.472
Started happening more and more,
so Dad went to go dig around.

10:38.555 --> 10:40.140
That was about three weeks ago.

10:40.640 --> 10:43.268
I hadn't heard from him since,
which is bad enough.

10:44.186 --> 10:46.063
Then I get this voicemail yesterday.

10:46.646 --> 10:50.650
JOHN: Dean. Something is starting
to happen. I think it's serious.

10:50.734 --> 10:52.986
I need to try and find out
what's going on.

10:53.862 --> 10:55.113
(VOICE MUFFLED)

10:56.698 --> 10:59.451
Be very careful, Dean.
We're all in danger.

11:00.410 --> 11:02.037
You know there's EVP on that?

11:02.120 --> 11:04.664
Not bad, Sammy.
Kind of like riding a bike, isn't it?

11:05.624 --> 11:08.710
All right, I slowed the message down
and ran it through GoldWave,

11:08.794 --> 11:10.754
took out the hiss and this is what I got.

11:12.339 --> 11:15.175
WOMAN: I can never go home.

11:18.095 --> 11:19.346
"Never go home."

11:25.143 --> 11:27.729
You know, in almost two years,
I've never bothered you,

11:27.813 --> 11:29.189
never asked you for a thing.

11:30.816 --> 11:31.858
(SIGHING)

11:36.446 --> 11:37.864
All right. I'll go.

11:39.866 --> 11:41.076
I'll help you find him.

11:41.159 --> 11:43.203
But I have to get back first thing Monday.

11:43.286 --> 11:44.538
Just wait here.

11:44.621 --> 11:46.039
What's first thing Monday?

11:47.040 --> 11:49.167
-I have an interview.
-What, a job interview?

11:49.251 --> 11:50.460
Skip it.

11:51.002 --> 11:55.215
It's a law school interview
and it's my whole future on a plate.

11:55.298 --> 11:56.591
Law school?

11:57.092 --> 11:58.427
So we got a deal or not?

12:02.097 --> 12:03.682
JESSICA: Wait, you're taking off?

12:03.765 --> 12:05.684
Is this about your dad? Is he all right?

12:05.767 --> 12:07.853
Yeah. You know,
just a little family drama.

12:08.645 --> 12:11.189
Your brother said he was
on some kinda hunting trip.

12:11.273 --> 12:13.567
Oh, yeah, he's just deer hunting
up at the cabin.

12:13.650 --> 12:16.987
He's probably got Jim, Jack
and Jose along with him.

12:17.070 --> 12:18.780
We're just gonna go bring him back.

12:18.864 --> 12:20.323
What about the interview?

12:20.407 --> 12:23.118
I'll make the interview.
This is only for a couple days.

12:23.201 --> 12:24.161
Sam. I mean, please.

12:24.286 --> 12:25.871
Just stop for a second.

12:27.289 --> 12:28.373
You sure you're okay?

12:28.457 --> 12:30.584
Hey, everything's gonna be okay.

12:30.667 --> 12:32.002
I promise.

12:35.422 --> 12:37.132
At least tell me where you're going.

12:37.841 --> 12:39.593
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)

12:46.183 --> 12:47.893
Amy, I can't come over tonight.

12:48.810 --> 12:51.104
Because I got work
in the morning, that's why.

12:52.814 --> 12:55.233
Okay, I miss it,
my dad's gonna have my ass.

12:55.317 --> 12:56.318
(LAUGHING)

13:01.239 --> 13:02.991
Hey, uh, Amy, let me call you back?

13:07.787 --> 13:08.872
(RADIO BREAKING UP)

13:11.958 --> 13:13.210
Car trouble or something?

13:18.715 --> 13:19.758
Take me home.

13:20.717 --> 13:22.010
Sure, get in.

13:36.733 --> 13:40.320
So, you coming, uh, from
a Halloween party or something?

13:43.365 --> 13:44.407
(LAUGHING)

13:44.908 --> 13:48.119
You know, um, a girl like you
really shouldn't be alone out here.

14:00.173 --> 14:01.258
I'm with you.

14:12.727 --> 14:14.062
Uh...

14:15.522 --> 14:17.023
Will you come home with me?

14:17.440 --> 14:20.402
Um, hell, yeah. (CHUCKLING)

14:38.128 --> 14:40.171
Come on. You don't live here.

14:41.840 --> 14:43.258
I can never go home.

14:43.341 --> 14:45.719
What? What are you talking about?

14:46.011 --> 14:47.220
Nobody even lives here.

14:48.054 --> 14:49.180
Huh, where do you live?

14:56.938 --> 14:57.981
That was good.

14:59.399 --> 15:00.650
Joke's over, okay.

15:04.154 --> 15:05.238
You want me to leave?

15:25.592 --> 15:26.635
Hello?

15:34.434 --> 15:35.477
(SCREAMING)

15:59.000 --> 16:00.001
(SCREAMING)

16:06.716 --> 16:11.763
(SCREAMING)

16:25.902 --> 16:27.946
Hey. You want breakfast?

16:28.613 --> 16:29.698
No, thanks.

16:30.573 --> 16:32.200
So how'd you pay for that stuff?

16:32.283 --> 16:34.661
You and Dad still running
credit card scams?

16:34.744 --> 16:37.497
Yeah, well, hunting ain't
exactly a pro ball career.

16:39.207 --> 16:42.544
Besides, all we do is apply.
It's not our fault they send us the cards.

16:42.627 --> 16:46.297
Yeah? And what names did you write
on the application this time?

16:46.381 --> 16:50.176
Uh, Burt Aframian and his son Hector.

16:50.635 --> 16:53.263
-Scored two cards out of the deal.
-Sounds about right.

16:54.139 --> 16:57.058
I swear, man. You gotta
update your cassette tape collection.

16:57.142 --> 16:59.602
-Why?
-Well, for one, they're cassette tapes.

16:59.686 --> 17:01.146
And two,

17:01.229 --> 17:04.983
Black Sabbath, MotÃ¶rhead, Metallica.

17:05.066 --> 17:07.277
It's the greatest hits of the mullet rock.

17:07.360 --> 17:09.279
Well, house rules, Sammy.

17:09.362 --> 17:10.572
Driver picks the music,

17:10.655 --> 17:12.323
shotgun shuts his cake hole.

17:12.991 --> 17:15.285
You know, "Sammy" is a chubby 12-year-old.
It's Sam, okay?

17:15.368 --> 17:16.411
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)

17:16.494 --> 17:18.663
Sorry, I can't hear you.
The music's too loud.

17:36.097 --> 17:39.350
All right, so there's no one matching Dad
at the hospital or morgue.

17:39.434 --> 17:41.144
So that's something, I guess.

17:44.105 --> 17:45.190
Check it out.

18:08.630 --> 18:09.631
Let's go.

18:13.927 --> 18:15.720
DEPUTY JAFFE: You guys find anything?

18:15.804 --> 18:17.430
No! Nothing!

18:23.436 --> 18:26.231
No sign of struggle.
No footprints. No fingerprints.

18:26.773 --> 18:28.566
It's spotless. It's almost too clean.

18:28.650 --> 18:31.236
So this kid, Troy,
he's dating your daughter, isn't he?

18:31.319 --> 18:33.071
-DEPUTY HEIN: Yeah.
-How's Amy doing?

18:33.154 --> 18:35.406
She's putting up
"Missing" posters downtown.

18:36.074 --> 18:39.244
You fellas had another one
like this just last month, didn't you?

18:40.328 --> 18:41.371
Who are you?

18:41.621 --> 18:42.872
Federal marshals.

18:44.916 --> 18:47.252
You two are little young
for marshals, aren't you?

18:47.335 --> 18:49.003
Thanks. That's awfully kind of you.

18:49.087 --> 18:51.381
You did have another
one just like this, correct?

18:51.589 --> 18:53.716
Yeah, that's right.
About a mile up the road.

18:53.800 --> 18:54.926
JAFFE: There've been others before that.

18:55.009 --> 18:57.178
So this victim, you knew him?

18:58.346 --> 19:00.014
Town like this, everybody knows everybody.

19:00.390 --> 19:03.643
Any connection between the victims,
besides that they're all men?

19:03.726 --> 19:05.436
No, not so far as we can tell.

19:05.520 --> 19:06.604
So what's the theory?

19:06.688 --> 19:08.231
JAFFE: Honestly? We don't know.

19:08.314 --> 19:09.941
Serial murder? Kidnapping ring?

19:10.024 --> 19:12.443
Well, that is exactly
the kind of crack police work

19:12.527 --> 19:14.445
-I'd expect out of you guys.
-(STAMPING)

19:15.029 --> 19:16.281
Thank you for your time.

19:17.448 --> 19:18.491
Gentlemen.

19:26.541 --> 19:27.584
Ow.

19:27.667 --> 19:29.627
-What was that for?
-Why you gotta step on my foot?

19:29.711 --> 19:31.504
Why do you talk to police like that?

19:31.588 --> 19:34.132
Come on. They don't really
know what's going on.

19:34.215 --> 19:36.551
We're all alone on this.
I mean, if we're gonna find Dad,

19:36.634 --> 19:38.553
we've gotta get to the bottom
of this thing ourselves.

19:40.722 --> 19:41.890
Can I help you boys?

19:43.182 --> 19:44.642
No, sir. We were just leaving.

19:45.059 --> 19:46.644
Agent Mulder. Agent Scully.

19:55.486 --> 19:58.072
-DEAN: I'll bet you that's her.
-Yeah.

19:59.908 --> 20:01.326
-You must be Amy.
-Yeah.

20:02.076 --> 20:05.204
Troy told us about you. We're his uncles.
I'm Dean. This is Sammy.

20:05.288 --> 20:06.873
He never mentioned you to me.

20:06.956 --> 20:08.374
Yeah, that's Troy, I guess.

20:08.458 --> 20:10.501
We're not around much,
we're up in Modesto.

20:10.585 --> 20:13.796
So we're looking for him too
and we're kind of asking around.

20:14.297 --> 20:15.840
-Hey, are you okay?
-Yeah.

20:16.257 --> 20:18.301
You mind if we ask you a couple questions?

20:19.385 --> 20:21.012
AMY: I was on the phone with Troy.

20:21.512 --> 20:22.805
He was driving home.

20:22.889 --> 20:24.641
He said he would call me right back.

20:24.724 --> 20:26.809
And, uh, he never did.

20:27.101 --> 20:29.771
He didn't say anything strange
or out of the ordinary?

20:30.355 --> 20:31.898
No, nothing I can remember.

20:33.191 --> 20:34.442
Here's the deal, ladies.

20:34.525 --> 20:37.695
The way Troy disappeared,
something's not right.

20:38.321 --> 20:39.822
So if you've heard anything...

20:41.866 --> 20:42.909
What is it?

20:43.868 --> 20:47.956
Well, it's just... I mean, with all
these guys going missing, people talk.

20:48.039 --> 20:49.540
BOTH: What do they talk about?

20:52.877 --> 20:54.462
It's kind of this local legend.

20:55.213 --> 20:59.425
This one girl, she got murdered
out on Centennial, like, decades ago.

21:00.510 --> 21:02.470
Well, supposedly she's still out there.

21:03.513 --> 21:04.555
She hitchhikes.

21:05.139 --> 21:06.474
And whoever picks her up,

21:07.475 --> 21:09.811
well, they disappear forever.

21:27.120 --> 21:28.746
-Let me try.
-Got it.

21:30.289 --> 21:31.499
Dude.

21:32.750 --> 21:34.335
You're such a control freak.

21:35.211 --> 21:37.797
So, angry spirits are born
out of violent death, right?

21:37.880 --> 21:39.924
-Yeah.
-Maybe it's not murder.

21:48.933 --> 21:51.936
This was 1981.
"Constance Welch, 24 years old,

21:52.020 --> 21:54.731
"jumps off Sylvania Bridge,
drowns in the river."

21:54.814 --> 21:56.441
-Does it say why she did it?
-Yeah.

21:56.524 --> 21:57.900
-What?
-(SAM EXHALES DEEPLY)

21:57.984 --> 22:00.111
An hour before they found her,
she calls 911.

22:00.194 --> 22:03.489
Her two little kids are in the bathtub.
She leaves them alone for a minute

22:03.573 --> 22:06.200
and when she comes back,
they aren't breathing.

22:06.784 --> 22:08.286
-Both die.
-Hmm.

22:08.661 --> 22:11.789
SAM: "'Our babies were gone,
and Constance just couldn't bear it,'

22:11.873 --> 22:13.583
"said husband, Joseph Welch."

22:14.333 --> 22:16.210
DEAN: That bridge look familiar to you?

22:21.799 --> 22:24.510
DEAN: So this is where
Constance took the swan dive.

22:24.594 --> 22:26.679
So you think Dad would have been here?

22:27.722 --> 22:30.349
Well, he's chasing the same story
and we're chasing him.

22:31.893 --> 22:33.144
Okay, so now what?

22:34.103 --> 22:36.898
Now, we keep digging till we find him.
Might take a while.

22:36.981 --> 22:39.567
Dean. I told you. I've gotta get back...

22:39.650 --> 22:40.735
BOTH: By Monday.

22:41.778 --> 22:43.821
-Right. The interview.
-Yeah.

22:43.905 --> 22:45.490
Yeah. I forgot.

22:45.573 --> 22:47.742
You're really serious
about this, aren't you?

22:48.451 --> 22:50.661
You think you're just gonna
become some lawyer?

22:51.162 --> 22:53.456
-Marry your girl?
-Maybe. Why not?

22:53.539 --> 22:55.416
Does Jessica know the truth about you?

22:55.500 --> 22:57.710
I mean, does she know
about things you've done?

22:57.794 --> 22:59.921
No.
And she's not ever going to know.

23:00.004 --> 23:01.297
Well, that's healthy.

23:01.631 --> 23:03.549
You can pretend all you want, Sammy.

23:03.633 --> 23:06.385
But, sooner or later, you're gonna
have to face up to who you really are.

23:06.469 --> 23:08.262
-And who's that?
-You're one of us.

23:08.346 --> 23:09.931
No. I'm not like you.

23:10.014 --> 23:12.934
-This is not going to be my life.
-You have a responsibility.

23:13.017 --> 23:15.269
To Dad? And his crusade?

23:15.853 --> 23:19.190
If it weren't for pictures, I wouldn't
even know what Mom looks like.

23:19.565 --> 23:21.109
What difference would it make?

23:21.192 --> 23:23.402
Even if we do find the thing
that killed her...

23:24.195 --> 23:26.781
Mom's gone, and she isn't coming back.

23:33.204 --> 23:34.747
Don't talk about her like that.

23:44.590 --> 23:45.883
Sam.

23:58.563 --> 24:00.064
-Where'd she go?
-I don't know.

24:00.148 --> 24:02.483
(CAR ENGINE STARTING)

24:04.610 --> 24:05.987
DEAN: What the...

24:06.487 --> 24:08.156
Who's driving your car?

24:11.576 --> 24:12.869
(TIRES SCREECHING)

24:16.414 --> 24:17.790
Dean! Go! Go!

24:37.101 --> 24:39.353
(SAM GASPING)

24:43.191 --> 24:44.525
Dean!

24:46.903 --> 24:48.779
Hey, are you all right?

24:50.114 --> 24:51.449
I'm super.

24:57.079 --> 24:58.206
SAM: Car all right?

24:58.289 --> 25:01.042
Yeah. Whatever she did to it,
it seems all right now.

25:01.125 --> 25:03.544
That Constance chick, what a bitch!

25:03.628 --> 25:06.547
Well, she doesn't want us
digging around, that's for sure.

25:08.424 --> 25:10.426
So where's the trail go from here, genius?

25:16.182 --> 25:17.934
You smell like a toilet.

25:20.686 --> 25:22.104
One room, please.

25:25.858 --> 25:27.985
You guys having a reunion or something?

25:28.069 --> 25:30.821
-What do you mean?
-That other guy, Burt Aframian.

25:30.905 --> 25:33.407
He came in and bought out
a room for the whole month.

25:34.283 --> 25:35.576
(LOCK CLICKING)

25:57.515 --> 25:58.724
Ugh.

26:00.226 --> 26:03.062
I don't think he's been here
for a couple of days, at least.

26:04.855 --> 26:07.358
Salt. Cat's-eye shells.

26:08.067 --> 26:11.237
He was worried.
Trying to keep something from coming in.

26:14.740 --> 26:16.117
What do you got here?

26:16.575 --> 26:18.452
Centennial Highway victims.

26:20.538 --> 26:22.081
I don't get it.

26:22.373 --> 26:25.835
They're different men,
different jobs, ages, ethnicities.

26:27.044 --> 26:28.796
There's always a connection, right?

26:29.630 --> 26:31.382
What do these guys have in common?

26:44.729 --> 26:45.896
(CHUCKLES)

26:46.230 --> 26:48.566
-Dad figured it out.
-What do you mean?

26:49.317 --> 26:50.985
He found the same article we did.

26:51.360 --> 26:54.405
Constance Welch.
She's our Woman in White.

26:57.450 --> 26:59.118
DEAN: You sly dogs.

26:59.285 --> 27:00.786
So if we are dealing
with a Woman in White,

27:00.870 --> 27:02.705
Dad would have found the corpse
and destroyed it.

27:02.788 --> 27:04.540
She might have another weakness.

27:04.999 --> 27:07.460
No, Dad would wanna make sure.
He'd dig her up.

27:07.543 --> 27:09.086
Does it say where she's buried?

27:09.170 --> 27:11.088
No. Not that I can tell.

27:11.630 --> 27:13.799
If I were Dad, though,
I'd go ask her husband.

27:14.300 --> 27:15.593
If he's still alive.

27:16.677 --> 27:17.845
DEAN: Hmm.

27:21.349 --> 27:24.018
All right, why don't you see
if you can find an address.

27:24.101 --> 27:25.311
I'm gonna get cleaned up.

27:25.728 --> 27:27.063
Hey, Dean?

27:27.438 --> 27:30.358
What I said earlier,
about Mom and Dad, I'm sorry.

27:31.484 --> 27:32.818
No chick-flick moments.

27:33.110 --> 27:35.780
(CHUCKLES) All right. Jerk.

27:36.989 --> 27:38.157
Bitch.

27:38.657 --> 27:39.825
(CHUCKLES)

27:55.174 --> 27:58.803
JESSICA: (ON VOICEMAIL) Hey, it's me.
It's about 10:20, Saturday night...

27:58.886 --> 28:01.889
Hey, man, I'm starving.
I'm gonna grab a little something to eat

28:01.972 --> 28:03.432
at that diner down the street.

28:03.516 --> 28:04.767
You want anything?

28:04.975 --> 28:06.560
-No.
-Aframian's buying.

28:06.769 --> 28:07.812
Mmm-mmm.

28:20.533 --> 28:22.451
(WOMAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
OVER POLICE RADIO)

28:24.495 --> 28:26.622
JESSICA: So come home soon, okay?
I love you.

28:26.705 --> 28:28.499
-(PHONE BEEPING)
-(EXHALES DEEPLY)

28:29.708 --> 28:31.544
-What?
-Dude. Five-0. Take off.

28:32.336 --> 28:34.588
-What about you?
-Ah, they kind of spotted me.

28:34.672 --> 28:35.840
Go find Dad.

28:38.050 --> 28:40.302
-Problem, officers?
-Where's your partner?

28:40.928 --> 28:42.805
Partner? What? What partner?

28:50.646 --> 28:54.024
So. Fake US Marshal. Fake credit cards.

28:54.358 --> 28:55.776
You got anything that's real?

28:56.235 --> 28:57.945
My boobs.

28:59.363 --> 29:01.157
JAFFE: You have the right
to remain silent.

29:01.240 --> 29:03.784
Anything you say can and will be
used against you in a court of law

29:03.909 --> 29:05.661
So you wanna give us your real name?

29:06.203 --> 29:09.081
I told you. It's Nugent.
Ted Nugent.

29:11.375 --> 29:14.420
I'm not sure you realize
just how much trouble you're in here.

29:14.962 --> 29:17.131
We talking, like,
misdemeanor kind of trouble?

29:17.214 --> 29:18.883
Or squeal-like-a-pig trouble?

29:18.966 --> 29:21.760
You got the faces of 10 missing persons
taped to your wall,

29:21.844 --> 29:24.263
along with a whole lot
of satanic mumbo jumbo.

29:24.930 --> 29:26.765
Boy, you are officially a suspect.

29:26.849 --> 29:28.058
That makes sense.

29:28.142 --> 29:31.061
'Cause when the first one
went missing in '82, I was three.

29:31.145 --> 29:34.315
I know you got partners.
One of them is an older guy.

29:34.398 --> 29:36.233
Maybe he started the whole thing.

29:37.776 --> 29:39.945
So tell me, Dean.

29:42.406 --> 29:43.491
Is this his?

29:50.956 --> 29:53.000
I thought that might be your name.

29:54.168 --> 29:55.961
See, I leafed through this.

29:56.045 --> 29:59.256
What little I could make out,
I mean, it's nine kinds of crazy.

30:00.925 --> 30:02.301
But I found this too.

30:03.636 --> 30:04.803
Now...

30:04.887 --> 30:06.847
You're staying right here
till you tell me

30:06.931 --> 30:09.016
exactly what the hell that means.

30:14.605 --> 30:17.525
-Hi, are you Joseph Welch?
-Yeah.

30:18.442 --> 30:20.444
JOSEPH: Yeah. He was older,
but that's him.

30:20.528 --> 30:22.279
Came by three or four days ago.

30:22.363 --> 30:23.948
Said he was a reporter.

30:24.031 --> 30:26.492
That's right.
We're working on a story together.

30:27.743 --> 30:30.829
Well, I don't know what the hell
kind of story you're working on.

30:30.913 --> 30:33.999
-The questions he asked me...
-About your late wife, Constance.

30:34.833 --> 30:36.418
He asked me where she was buried.

30:37.461 --> 30:39.046
And where is that again?

30:39.588 --> 30:41.173
I gotta go through this twice?

30:41.549 --> 30:43.509
It's fact-checking. If you don't mind.

30:46.470 --> 30:49.557
In a plot behind my old place,
over on Breckenridge.

30:50.391 --> 30:51.892
Why did you move?

30:53.644 --> 30:56.730
I'm not gonna live in the house
where my children died.

30:59.567 --> 31:01.360
Mr. Welch, did you ever marry again?

31:01.443 --> 31:02.444
No way.

31:03.279 --> 31:05.155
Constance, she was the love of my life.

31:07.074 --> 31:08.534
Prettiest woman I ever known.

31:08.993 --> 31:10.578
So you had a happy marriage?

31:13.998 --> 31:15.374
Definitely.

31:16.458 --> 31:17.835
(SAM INHALES DEEPLY)

31:17.918 --> 31:20.087
Well, that should do it.
Thanks for your time.

31:27.511 --> 31:28.929
(KEYS JANGLING)

31:31.015 --> 31:33.183
Mr. Welch, you ever hear
of a Woman in White?

31:34.268 --> 31:36.437
-A what?
-A Woman in White.

31:36.854 --> 31:38.355
Or sometimes Weeping Woman?

31:39.648 --> 31:41.483
It's a ghost story. Well... (CHUCKLES)

31:42.192 --> 31:44.069
It's more of a phenomenon, really.

31:44.361 --> 31:45.487
They're spirits.

31:45.571 --> 31:49.158
They've been sighted
for hundreds of years, dozens of places.

31:49.241 --> 31:52.286
In Hawaii, in Mexico.
Lately, in Arizona, Indiana.

31:52.369 --> 31:54.538
All these are different women,
you understand,

31:54.622 --> 31:56.040
but all share the same story.

31:57.458 --> 32:00.210
Boy, I don't care much for nonsense.

32:00.628 --> 32:02.296
See, when they were alive,

32:02.379 --> 32:04.256
their husbands were unfaithful to them.

32:05.591 --> 32:06.759
And these women,

32:06.842 --> 32:08.927
basically suffering
from temporary insanity,

32:09.011 --> 32:10.262
murdered their children.

32:11.722 --> 32:15.017
Then once they realized what they
had done, they took their own lives.

32:15.434 --> 32:17.394
So now their spirits are cursed.

32:17.478 --> 32:19.313
Walking backroads, waterways.

32:19.813 --> 32:22.483
And if they find an unfaithful man,
they kill him.

32:23.317 --> 32:24.985
And that man is never seen again.

32:26.779 --> 32:28.489
You think...

32:29.490 --> 32:31.700
You think that has something to do with...

32:31.784 --> 32:33.077
Constance,

32:33.661 --> 32:34.828
you smart-ass?

32:35.496 --> 32:36.664
You tell me.

32:40.042 --> 32:41.460
I mean, maybe,

32:42.127 --> 32:43.837
maybe I made some mistakes.

32:45.089 --> 32:46.507
But no matter what I did,

32:47.091 --> 32:49.802
Constance, she never would have
killed her own children.

32:51.595 --> 32:53.180
Now you get the hell out of here.

32:54.223 --> 32:55.933
And you don't come back.

32:57.851 --> 32:59.812
(BREATHING DEEPLY)

33:11.156 --> 33:13.283
I don't know how many times
I gotta tell you,

33:13.367 --> 33:14.993
it's my high school locker combo.

33:15.369 --> 33:17.121
We gonna do this all night long?

33:17.204 --> 33:20.040
We just got a 911.
Shots fired over at Whiteford Road.

33:22.000 --> 33:23.544
You have to go to the bathroom?

33:24.169 --> 33:25.879
-No.
-Good.

33:44.982 --> 33:46.483
SHERIFF PIERCE: Let's go.

33:52.364 --> 33:54.158
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

33:59.913 --> 34:03.167
Fake 911 phone call, Sammy?
I don't know. That's pretty illegal.

34:03.250 --> 34:05.419
-You're welcome.
-Listen, we gotta talk.

34:05.502 --> 34:08.130
Tell me about it.
So the husband was unfaithful.

34:08.213 --> 34:10.007
We are dealing with a Woman in White.

34:10.090 --> 34:11.258
And she's buried behind her old house,

34:11.341 --> 34:12.468
so that should've been Dad's next stop.

34:12.551 --> 34:13.927
Sammy, would you shut up for a second?

34:14.011 --> 34:16.305
I just can't figure out why he hasn't
destroyed the corpse yet.

34:16.388 --> 34:17.514
DEAN: Well,
that's what I'm trying to tell you.

34:17.639 --> 34:19.141
He's gone.

34:19.224 --> 34:20.768
-Dad left Jericho.
-What?

34:20.851 --> 34:21.935
How do you know?

34:22.728 --> 34:23.729
I've got his journal.

34:23.812 --> 34:25.773
He doesn't go anywhere
without that thing.

34:25.856 --> 34:28.025
-Yeah, well, he did this time.
-What's it say?

34:28.108 --> 34:29.234
DEAN: Same old ex-Marine crap,

34:29.318 --> 34:30.778
when he wants to let us know
where he's going.

34:30.861 --> 34:32.654
Coordinates.
Where to?

34:32.738 --> 34:33.781
I'm not sure yet.

34:33.864 --> 34:35.866
Dean, what the hell is going on?

34:35.949 --> 34:37.576
-Whoa.
-(BRAKES SCREECHING)

34:39.369 --> 34:40.621
Sam! Sam!

34:47.085 --> 34:48.212
Take me home.

34:54.468 --> 34:56.220
Take me home.

34:58.013 --> 34:59.181
No.

35:04.353 --> 35:05.354
(SAM PANTING)

35:34.883 --> 35:36.093
Don't do this.

35:38.637 --> 35:40.264
I can never go home.

35:42.099 --> 35:43.642
You're scared to go home.

35:51.066 --> 35:52.484
Hold me.

35:53.235 --> 35:54.653
I'm so cold.

35:56.071 --> 35:57.656
But you can't kill me.

35:57.906 --> 35:59.408
I'm not unfaithful.

36:00.284 --> 36:01.785
I've never been.

36:03.203 --> 36:04.663
You will be.

36:22.514 --> 36:25.100
(SCREAMING)

36:25.434 --> 36:27.436
(GROANING)

36:45.621 --> 36:46.788
I'm taking you home.

36:49.583 --> 36:50.834
Sam!

37:01.136 --> 37:03.055
-Sam!
-Here.

37:03.138 --> 37:04.389
You okay?

37:04.806 --> 37:06.767
-I think.
-Can you move?

37:06.850 --> 37:08.268
(GROANING) Yeah. Help me.

37:18.737 --> 37:20.697
-(SAM GROANING)
-DEAN: There you go.

37:32.292 --> 37:34.419
(GROANING)

38:09.788 --> 38:12.040
TOGETHER: You've come home to us, Mommy.

38:19.506 --> 38:22.467
(SCREAMING)

38:39.818 --> 38:41.570
(GRUNTING)

38:49.953 --> 38:51.747
So this is where she drowned her kids.

38:53.749 --> 38:55.584
That's why she could never go home.

38:56.793 --> 38:58.378
She was too scared to face them.

38:59.755 --> 39:01.214
You found her weak spot.

39:01.757 --> 39:02.966
Nice work, Sammy.

39:03.050 --> 39:04.885
(LAUGHING)

39:05.385 --> 39:07.387
Yeah, I wish I could say the same for you.

39:07.471 --> 39:10.432
What were you thinking,
shooting Casper in the face, you freak?

39:10.515 --> 39:12.517
Hey. Saved your ass.

39:12.768 --> 39:13.810
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)

39:13.894 --> 39:16.605
I'll tell you another thing.
If you screwed up my car...

39:18.273 --> 39:19.483
I'll kill you.

39:19.566 --> 39:20.901
(CHUCKLING)

39:31.828 --> 39:35.457
SAM: Okay, here's where Dad went.
It's called Blackwater Ridge, Colorado.

39:36.625 --> 39:38.085
Sounds charming. How far?

39:39.252 --> 39:40.837
About 600 miles.

39:41.797 --> 39:43.840
If we shag ass, we can make it by morning.

39:46.051 --> 39:47.302
Dean, um...

39:49.805 --> 39:52.557
-You're not going.
-The interview's in, like, 10 hours.

39:52.641 --> 39:54.017
I gotta be there.

39:58.647 --> 39:59.731
Yeah.

40:00.107 --> 40:02.442
Yeah, whatever. I'll take you home.

40:23.630 --> 40:25.549
Maybe I can meet up with you later, huh?

40:25.632 --> 40:26.842
Yeah, all right.

40:28.385 --> 40:29.845
(ENGINE STARTS)

40:30.345 --> 40:31.388
Sam?

40:34.766 --> 40:37.144
You know, we made
a hell of a team back there.

40:37.561 --> 40:38.770
Yeah.

40:51.992 --> 40:53.785
-(KEYS JANGLING)
-(DOOR OPENING)

40:56.955 --> 40:58.206
Jess?

40:59.916 --> 41:01.126
You home?

41:04.421 --> 41:06.715
(SHOWER RUNNING)

41:30.655 --> 41:31.698
No!

41:34.576 --> 41:36.703
-Sam!
-Jess!

41:38.121 --> 41:39.873
Sam! Sam!

41:40.874 --> 41:42.834
-No! No!
-We gotta get out of here!

41:43.585 --> 41:45.837
Jess! Jess! No!

41:56.431 --> 41:58.516
(COUGHING)

42:29.422 --> 42:31.174
We got work to do.
